From: WangYunchao <wangyc@local>
Subject: [PATCH] streamdumper: gate dump write on sentinel file

Avoid dumping "fake" frames from session-restore / ad landing pages /
about:home during firefox startup. StreamDumper now only writes dump
files after a sentinel file appears, which BiDi creates when the
target video element reaches readyState>=3 + currentTime>1.

Mechanism:
- sDumpEnabled static flag (default false)
- Every 50 video samples / 100 audio samples: access("/tmp/firefox-stream-dump-enabled")
- If file exists: sDumpEnabled = true, start writing on next sample
- Otherwise: drop sample silently, no dump file created

Exposed:
- extern "C" void SetStreamDumpEnabled(bool)
- extern "C" bool QueryStreamDumpEnabled()

BiDi side will register a "streamDumper.enable" command that creates
the sentinel file (so firefox's BiDi JS layer doesn't need to call
into C++ directly).